# Stellar Dominion — Architecture

## Autoload Registry
These autoloads are registered in project.godot. Never create a second instance of these.

| Autoload Name | File | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| `ResourceManager` | `autoloads/resource_manager.gd` | Monthly tick, all resource balances |
| `SelectionManager` | `autoloads/selection_manager.gd` | Selected ships/fleets, selection state |
| `TechManager` | `autoloads/tech_manager.gd` | Researched nodes, unlock checks |
| `LeaderManager` | `autoloads/leader_manager.gd` | All leaders, council state, agendas |
| `EventBus` | `autoloads/event_bus.gd` | Global signal relay for cross-system events |
| `GameState` | `autoloads/game_state.gd` | Current date, game speed, pause state |

## Scene Structure
```
Main.tscn
├── GalaxyView.tscn          # Hyperlane map, star nodes, fleet icons
│   ├── GalaxyCamera         # Camera2D — pan/zoom
│   ├── HyperlaneRenderer    # Line2D drawing
│   ├── SystemLayer          # All StarSystemNode instances
│   ├── FleetLayer           # All FleetGalaxyIcon instances
│   └── SelectionHandler     # Box/click select logic
├── PlanetView.tscn          # Colony management
├── TechTreeView.tscn        # Research UI
├── LeaderView.tscn          # Leader roster, council
└── UIOverlay.tscn           # HUD, resource bar, alerts
```

## Resource (Data) Pattern
Game data lives in `.tres` / `.res` files, not in scripts.

```gdscript
# BuildingTierConfig — one .tres per building tier
class_name BuildingTierConfig
extends Resource

@export_group("Output")
@export var base_output: float = 0.0
@export var output_resource: String = ""

@export_group("Cost")
@export var construction_cost: Dictionary = {}
@export var upkeep_cost: Dictionary = {}

@export_group("Jobs")
@export var job_slots: Array[JobSlotData] = []
```

- Resources are embedded in building scenes via `@export var config: BuildingTierConfig`
- Never load `.tres` files at runtime with hardcoded paths — use `@export` on the parent scene

## Building Scene Hierarchy
```
BuildingBase.tscn (parent)
└── 28 inherited building scenes
    Each carries its own BuildingTierConfig resources per tier
    Root node exposes @export global_output_multiplier: float = 1.0
```

## Signal Convention via EventBus
Cross-system events go through `EventBus` autoload — never direct node references across scenes.

```gdscript
# Emitting
EventBus.building_completed.emit(building_id, planet_id)

# Connecting
EventBus.building_completed.connect(_on_building_completed)
```

## File Organization
```
stellar_dominion/
├── autoloads/
├── scenes/
│   ├── galaxy/
│   ├── planet/
│   ├── ui/
│   └── shared/
├── scripts/
│   ├── resources/       # .gd files for custom Resources
│   └── components/      # Reusable node scripts
├── data/
│   ├── buildings/       # .tres files
│   ├── leaders/
│   └── tech/
└── assets/
```

## Groups
Nodes must be added to these groups for cross-system queries:
- `"galaxy_ships"` — all fleet icons on the galaxy map
- `"star_systems"` — all StarSystemNode instances
- `"buildings"` — all active building nodes on planets
- `"leaders"` — all active leader nodes
